It is a firewall configuration tool that runs on top of iptables.

$ sudo ufw status
Status: inactive

$ sudo ufw enable
Firewall is active and enabled on system startup

$ sudo ufw status
Status: active
Logging: on (low)
Default: deny (incoming), allow (outgoing), deny (routed)
New profiles: skip

$ sudo ufw allow 22
$ sudo ufw allow ssh
$ sudo ufw allow http
$ sudo ufw allow https
$ sudo ufw allow OpenSSH

$ sudo ufw disable
